.TH MINIOS-KERNEL-MANAGER 1 "August 2025" "MiniOS Linux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
minios-kernel-manager \- Graphical tool for managing MiniOS kernels
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B minios-kernel-manager
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B minios-kernel-manager
 is a GTK3 graphical utility that provides a user-friendly interface for managing Linux kernels in the MiniOS distribution. It uses the 
.BR minios-kernel (1)
CLI backend via JSON API for all kernel operations.
.PP
The application provides an easy-to-use GTK3 interface for:
.IP \(bu 2
Visual selection of kernels with color-coded status indicators.
.IP \(bu 2
Real-time progress monitoring during kernel packaging operations.
.IP \(bu 2
Safe kernel activation with protection of running kernels.
.IP \(bu 2
Support for both repository packages and local .deb files.
.IP \(bu 2
Configurable compression settings for SquashFS and initramfs.
.IP \(bu 2
Context menu for kernel management (activate, delete operations).
.IP \(bu 2
Clean logging without technical prefixes for better user experience.
.SH ARCHITECTURE
The application follows a modern GUI-CLI architecture:
.IP \(bu 2
GUI communicates with CLI via JSON API for structured data exchange.
.IP \(bu 2
All kernel operations are performed by the
.BR minios-kernel (1)
backend.
.IP \(bu 2
Progress information is transmitted via JSON messages for real-time updates.
.IP \(bu 2
Fallback to text parsing ensures compatibility with older CLI versions.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /minios/kernels/{version}/
Repository for inactive packaged kernels.
.TP
.I /minios/config.conf.d/kernel-manager.conf
Configuration file storing the ACTIVE_KERNEL variable.
.TP
.I /usr/share/applications/minios-kernel-manager.desktop
Desktop entry file.
.TP
.I /usr/share/polkit-1/actions/dev.minios.kernel-manager.policy
PolicyKit policy file for privilege escalation.
.TP
.I /usr/share/minios-kernel-manager/style.css
Application stylesheet for custom GUI styling.
